  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Immediate food allergy is , sometimes , a life threatening situation . Diagnosis is done by
      skin prick test with commercial extracts. Nevertheless, some of the extracts are not optimal
      and reproduce false negative results (no allergy) in patients with history highly suggestive
      of allergic reaction. The aim of this study is to compare the reproducibility of different
      commercial extracts and raw food in patients with convincing history of acute allergic
      symptoms related to food .
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
